<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="213" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,258,829]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,768,793]" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some specimens from Guyana and Suriname (Appendix) seem to be intermediate between 
<taxonomicName box="[1341,1435,769,792]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="actorion">
<emphasis box="[1341,1435,769,792]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,322,804,828]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decaerulea">
<emphasis box="[198,322,804,828]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">decaerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see explanation in 
<taxonomicName box="[548,745,805,828]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Bia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="actorion" subSpecies="actorion">
<emphasis box="[548,745,805,828]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="213">actorion actorion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subspecies account above).
</paragraph>
